ans Were Funny And Didn't Wish Death On People", "last_comment_created": 1777338556980, "content": "", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 3, "score_up": 62, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"description": "U.S. \u2014 On the heels of yet another attempted act of political violence being used for laughs by late-night talk show hosts, Americans expressed a deep longing for the good old days when comedians were funny and didn't wish death on people.", "large_image": "0DsKDsej6U4dlAUV.png", "title": "Nation Longs For Good Old Days When Comedians Were Funny And Didn't Wish Death On People"}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "text", "uuid": "1ASZaTjKTx", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 26, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8586119, "raw_content": "I get it. It's hard, but it shows how crappy our ground game is here. Democrats filed endless lawsuits to stop the Ballroom and now they're saying the assassination attempt was staged to get it built. Judges are giving Venezuelans and Syrians priority access to green cards.\n\nWhat are we doing? How pathetic is the GOP they can't find a single black guy in VA who voted for Trump to and can claim standing here?\n\nEdit, I know as a Christian how this is all gonna end. That being said, what is the GOP even doing?", "author": "agave_lime", "created": 1777350010537, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "Counterwhat", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "titl